-- Pound Weakens Against Dollar, Euro After U.K. Inflation Report
-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 2013-07-16T08:35:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-16/pound-weakens-against-dollar-euro-after-u-k-inflation-report.html
The pound weakened against the
dollar and euro after a report showed U.K inflation accelerated
less than economists forecast in June. Consumer prices rose 2.9
percent from a year earlier, compared with 2.7 percent in May,
the Office for National Statistics said.  Sterling fell 0.3 percent to $1.5053 at 9:33 a.m. London
time. It declined 0.3 percent to 86.79 pence per euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucy Meakin in London at 
